Information regarding rusting in apple
KccAns: Rusting of apples in a humid environment is a major concern of the fruit growers Rusting occurs shortly after petal fall The apple cultivars which have thin cuticle are more susceptible to rusting It is commonly noticed on exposed fruits than on fruits remaining in shade Frost during the blossom or at the early fruit formation stage may also cause rusting Rusting leads to rupture of the fruit skin and development of cracks Control : Selection of less susceptible clones and adequate irrigation manuring and effective pest management can reduce rusting
